  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "What are Progress and Meter?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "The <progress> and <meter> elements are used to visually represent values. Progress shows task completion, while meter shows a value within a known range."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Progress Element"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "The <progress> tag represents the completion progress of a task."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<progress value=\"70\" max=\"100\"></progress>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Progress Example with Label"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<label>Loading:</label>\n<progress value=\"40\" max=\"100\"></progress>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Meter Element"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "The <meter> tag represents a scalar value within a known range, such as battery level or score."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<meter value=\"0.6\">60%</meter>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Meter with Range"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<meter min=\"0\" max=\"100\" value=\"70\"></meter>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Meter with Low, High, Optimum"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<meter min=\"0\" max=\"100\" low=\"30\" high=\"80\" optimum=\"90\" value=\"75\"></meter>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Key Differences"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "value": {
        "headers": ["Feature", "Progress", "Meter"],
